LINK_TEXT.0: ICON EUV Retrieved Dayside Ionosphere Products

Logical_source_description.0: ICON EUV derived ionospheric data products

TEXT.0: ICON explores the boundary between Earth and space (the ionosphere) to understand the physical connection between our world and the immediate space environment around us. Visit https://icon.ssl.berkeley.edu for more details.

TITLE.0: ICON EUV Daytime Ionosphere Products L2.6

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The daily F10.7 values used in the retrieval, in solar flux units. The data are obtained directly from The Solar Radio Monitoring Program through Natural Resources Canada (https://www.spaceweather.gc.ca/solarflux/sx-en.php).

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Custom F10.7a value used in the retrieval, in solar flux units. This value is constructed at the ICON Science Data Center and is meant to provide a timely approximation to the 81-day F10.7a average used in atmospheric models, but is centered on a date 33 days prior to the ICON measurement, specifically encompassing F10.7 data from 73 days prior to 7 days after the measurement.

VarAttributes.NC_STRINGS_V: CatDesc Depend_0 Display_Type FieldNam Long_Name Units Var_Notes Var_Type

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Quality flag associated with the L2 retrieval and/or L1 data. 0 = No issues reported,  1 = Moderate issue(s) identified, use results with caution, 2 = Severe issue(s) identified, recommend not using data product for this profile. See the ICON_L26_Flag_Details variable for additional information for the reported causes on any non-zero values
